    {
      "id": "props_box", "type": "rectangle", "x": 555, "y": 120, "width": 310, "height": 280,
      "angle": 0, "strokeColor": "#1971c2", "backgroundColor": "#dbe4ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid", "strokeWidth": 1, "strokeStyle": "solid", "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100, "groupIds": [], "frameId": null, "index": "aA",
      "roundness": {"type": 3}, "seed": 11001, "version": 1, "versionNonce": 11002,
      "isDeleted": false, "boundElements": [{"id": "t_props", "type": "text"}],
      "updated": 1774700000000, "link": null, "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "t_props", "type": "text", "x": 560, "y": 128, "width": 300, "height": 265,
      "angle": 0, "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e", "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid", "strokeWidth": 1, "strokeStyle": "solid", "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100, "groupIds": [], "frameId": null, "index": "aAa", "roundness": null,
      "seed": 11003, "version": 1, "versionNonce": 11004, "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null, "updated": 1774700000000, "link": null, "locked": false,
      "text": "Lock-free:\n  No mutex, no spinlock.\n  Only atomic load/store on head & tail.\n\nSPSC contract:\n  Exactly 1 writer thread.\n  Exactly 1 reader thread.\n  Violating this = undefined behavior.\n\nMemory ordering:\n  Writer: store tail with release\n  Reader: load tail with acquire\n  → guarantees data visibility\n\nWrap-around:\n  head/tail are monotonic counters.\n  Actual index = counter % capacity.\n  No modulo needed if capacity is 2^N.\n\nEmpty: head == tail\nFull:  tail - head == capacity\n\nZero-copy capable:\n  Reader can get pointer to data\n  without memcpy (peek API).",
      "originalText": "Lock-free:\n  No mutex, no spinlock.\n  Only atomic load/store on head & tail.\n\nSPSC contract:\n  Exactly 1 writer thread.\n  Exactly 1 reader thread.\n  Violating this = undefined behavior.\n\nMemory ordering:\n  Writer: store tail with release\n  Reader: load tail with acquire\n  → guarantees data visibility\n\nWrap-around:\n  head/tail are monotonic counters.\n  Actual index = counter % capacity.\n  No modulo needed if capacity is 2^N.\n\nEmpty: head == tail\nFull:  tail - head == capacity\n\nZero-copy capable:\n  Reader can get pointer to data\n  without memcpy (peek API).",
      "autoResize": true, "fontSize": 11, "fontFamily": 2, "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "middle", "containerId": "props_box", "lineHeight": 1.25
    },

    {
      "id": "variants_box", "type": "rectangle", "x": 40, "y": 450, "width": 840, "height": 100,
      "angle": 0, "strokeColor": "#862e9c", "backgroundColor": "#f3d9fa",
      "fillStyle": "solid", "strokeWidth": 2, "strokeStyle": "solid", "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100, "groupIds": [], "frameId": null, "index": "aB",
      "roundness": {"type": 3}, "seed": 12001, "version": 1, "versionNonce": 12002,
      "isDeleted": false, "boundElements": [{"id": "t_variants", "type": "text"}],
      "updated": 1774700000000, "link": null, "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "t_variants", "type": "text", "x": 45, "y": 458, "width": 830, "height": 85,
      "angle": 0, "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e", "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid", "strokeWidth": 1, "strokeStyle": "solid", "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100, "groupIds": [], "frameId": null, "index": "aBa", "roundness": null,
      "seed": 12003, "version": 1, "versionNonce": 12004, "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null, "updated": 1774700000000, "link": null, "locked": false,
      "text": "Ouroboros Ring Buffer Variants:\n\n  spsc::RingBuffer    1 writer, 1 reader    Lock-free (atomics only)     Used by aether IPC (IpcRing)\n  mpsc::RingBuffer    N writers, 1 reader    Lock-free (CAS on tail)      For multi-producer logging / event queues\n  spmc::RingBuffer    1 writer, N readers    Lock-free (CAS on head)      For fan-out / broadcast patterns",
      "originalText": "Ouroboros Ring Buffer Variants:\n\n  spsc::RingBuffer    1 writer, 1 reader    Lock-free (atomics only)     Used by aether IPC (IpcRing)\n  mpsc::RingBuffer    N writers, 1 reader    Lock-free (CAS on tail)      For multi-producer logging / event queues\n  spmc::RingBuffer    1 writer, N readers    Lock-free (CAS on head)      For fan-out / broadcast patterns",
      "originalText": "Ouroboros Ring Buffer Variants:\n\n  spsc::RingBuffer    1 writer, 1 reader    Lock-free (atomics only)     Used by aether IPC (IpcRing)\n  mpsc::RingBuffer    N writers, 1 reader    Lock-free (CAS on tail)      For multi-producer logging / event queues\n  spmc::RingBuffer    1 writer, N readers    Lock-free (CAS on head)      For fan-out / broadcast patterns",
      "autoResize": true, "fontSize": 12, "fontFamily": 3, "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "middle", "containerId": "variants_box", "lineHeight": 1.25
    },

    {
      "id": "aether_note", "type": "rectangle", "x": 40, "y": 580, "width": 840, "height": 70,
      "angle": 0, "strokeColor": "#1971c2", "backgroundColor": "#dbe4ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid", "strokeWidth": 2, "strokeStyle": "dashed", "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100, "groupIds": [], "frameId": null, "index": "aC",
      "roundness": {"type": 3}, "seed": 13001, "version": 1, "versionNonce": 13002,
      "isDeleted": false, "boundElements": [{"id": "t_aether", "type": "text"}],
      "updated": 1774700000000, "link": null, "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "t_aether", "type": "text", "x": 45, "y": 588, "width": 830, "height": 55,
      "angle": 0, "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e", "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid", "strokeWidth": 1, "strokeStyle": "solid", "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100, "groupIds": [], "frameId": null, "index": "aCa", "roundness": null,
      "seed": 13003, "version": 1, "versionNonce": 13004, "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null, "updated": 1774700000000, "link": null, "locked": false,
      "text": "In Aether IPC: two spsc::RingBuffer instances are placement-new'd into shared memory (512KB total).\nRing 0 (256KB): client → server (requests).  Ring 1 (256KB): server → client (responses + notifications).\nServiceBase uses sendMutex to serialize txRing writes — making the server side act as a single producer despite\nmultiple code paths (receiverLoop responses + sendNotify broadcasts) writing to the same ring.",
      "originalText": "In Aether IPC: two spsc::RingBuffer instances are placement-new'd into shared memory (512KB total).\nRing 0 (256KB): client → server (requests).  Ring 1 (256KB): server → client (responses + notifications).\nServiceBase uses sendMutex to serialize txRing writes — making the server side act as a single producer despite\nmultiple code paths (receiverLoop responses + sendNotify broadcasts) writing to the same ring.",
      "autoResize": true, "fontSize": 11, "fontFamily": 2, "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "middle", "containerId": "aether_note", "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
